			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2016</a> paper:</span><br><i>Execution Framework of the GEMOC Studio (Tool Demo)</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ErwanBousse.html">Erwan Bousse</a>, <a href="../profile/ThomasDegueule.html">Thomas Degueule</a>, <a href="../profile/DidierVojtisek.html">Didier Vojtisek</a>, <a href="../profile/TanjaMayerhofer.html">Tanja Mayerhofer</a>, <a href="../profile/JulienDeAntoni.html">Julien DeAntoni</a>, <a href="../profile/BenoîtCombemale.html">Benoît Combemale</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/2997364.2997384">10.1145/2997364.2997384</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It demonstrates the GEMOC Studio’s execution framework as a meta-tool for engineering executable DSMLs.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4d.html"><span class="tagL">T4D: Interpretation</span></a><ul><li> It provides runtime services for executing DSML semantics (e.g., debugging).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4e.html"><span class="tagL">T4E: Simulation</span></a><ul><li> The framework supports execution-related services such as simulation/animation of DSML models.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL">T4F: Visualisation</span></a><ul><li> It includes graphical animation/visual feedback as part of the execution tooling.
</li></ul></li></ul>
